properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 11 at 3:54AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
Cold air will move south through British Columbia this weekend. On
Sunday, a weather system will arrive as cold Fraser outflow develops.
Rain will change to snow in the Bellingham area and in the San
Juans on Sunday. Cold wind chills will develop and blowing snow
will be possible around Bellingham and in the San Juans.

Cold air will spread south through the rest of Western Washington
Sunday night along the modified arctic front. Temperatures that fall
below freezing can lead to icy roads after even light snowfall.

Areas along the coast and across Southwest Washington will not
avoid the cold snap. A weather system moving into Oregon on
Monday could affect southwest Washington. At this time it looks
like most of the moisture with that weather system will remain in
Oregon but stay tuned to updated weather forecasts and prepare
for wintry weather.

NWSheadline: COLD WEATHER WITH A CHANCE OF LOWLAND SNOW
